New York Times / May 06, 2024, 13:53 (IST)

All vaccines have at least occasional side effects. But people who say they were injured by Covid vaccines believe their cases have been ignored

Free-market ex-UK Treasury chief Nigel Lawson dies

AP / Apr 04, 2023, 16:21 (IST)

Nigel Lawson, former UK Treasury Chief under Margaret Thatcher, died at the age of 91. Lawson led the Treasury from 1983-1989 and championed the move to put public sector businesses in private control, as well as the modernisation of financial markets in a wave of deregulation known as the Big Bang.

Jada Pinkett Smith and Black women's hair: History of disrespect leads to the CROWN Act

PTI / Apr 06, 2022, 14:12 (IST)

The fallout from 'the slap' at this year's Oscars continues. Last week, Will Smith resigned from the Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences, after the academy issued a statement condemning Smith's actions.

'Headless body in topless bar': Author of iconic headline dies

TNN / Jun 11, 2015, 06:52 (IST)

Headline writers are a damned lot. Time is tight, wordage limited, and against the ticking of the clock and constraints of space, they have to confect a headline that captures, accurately, the substance of the story, however long and complex the narrative might be.
